about_favourite_technologies: Here are some tools and technologies I am interested in at the moment
about_paragraph:
My name is Qasim, and I am a second-year Computing Science student at the University of Alberta. 

Working with various tools and technologies is my passion, and I've been honing my skills since 2017. I have experience working in high-paced environments, and I thrive when working under pressure.

I am also passionate about sharing knowledge on topics in computer science and software development. I've realized that explaining hard to understand concepts is the most effective way for me to learn. 

I am currently working on my Medium blog to document my journey of discovering exciting topics in computer science and software development. This site is a part of a demo for my article on the Globalization of software.

Over the past year, I have also worked at Intuit as a co-op Software Developer on the Globalization Team. This team is the one that works on exciting new innovations and the scalable infrastructure to help enable Intuit to go global.
